--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages mlocate.

mlocate is a locate/updatedb implementation. It keeps a database of all existing
files and allows you to lookup files by name. The 'm' stands for "merging":
updatedb reuses the existing database to avoid rereading most of the file system,
which makes updatedb faster and does not trash the system caches as much as
traditional locate implementations.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: mlocate
       mlocate_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: mlocate
       mlocate_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  mlocate_state
    Specify predetermined 'mlocate_state' variable (string).

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
